nt to the User&rsquo;s account in order to begin the work. To complete or end the work, the Service Provider must request for an One Time Password (OTP) and after sharing such OTP, the amount will be credited to the Service Providers wallet which they can redeem or withdraw at any point of time, in the future, keeping the below mentioned clauses in mind.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Content on the Site<br />\r\n2.1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;You understand that all information, data, text, sound, photographs, graphics, video, messages, software, tags, advertisements or other materials (&ldquo;Content&rdquo;), whether publicly posted or privately transmitted, are the sole responsibility of the person from whom such Content originated. This means that you, and not AntsNest, are entirely responsible for all Content that you upload, post, transmit or otherwise make available through the AntsNest Services.<br />\r\n2.2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;We do not control the Content posted through the AntsNest Services and, as such, we do not guarantee the accuracy, integrity or quality of such Content and disclaim any and all liability in connection with such Content. The opinions expressed in postings or other Content provided through the AntsNest Services are not necessarily those of AntsNest or its owner, content providers, advertisers, sponsors, affiliated or related entities. You understand that by using the AntsNest Services you may be exposed to Content that is offensive, indecent or objectionable. You understand that we are not obligated to pre-screen, regularly review, monitor, delete or otherwise change the Content associated with the AntsNest Services. We do, however, reserve the right to do so at any time in our sole discretion, for any reason or no reason, and to delete any Content with or without notice. Under no circumstances will we be liable in any way for any Content, including, but not limited to, any errors or omissions in any Content, or any loss or damage of any kind incurred as a result of the use of any Content posted, emailed, transmitted or otherwise made available through the AntsNest Services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsibility for Your Content (Professionals Content)<br />\r\n3.1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;You are solely responsible for the Content you submit or make available for inclusion through the AntsNest Services (&ldquo;Professionals Content&ldquo;) and the consequences of posting or publishing it. In connection with Professionals Content, you represent and warrant that you own or have the necessary licenses, rights, consents, and permissions to use and authorize AntsNest to use all trademark, copyright or other intellectual property rights in and to any and all Professionals Content to enable inclusion and use of the Professionals Content in the manner intended by the AntsNest Services and the Terms of Use. You agree that you will not submit Professionals Content that violates these Terms of Use.<br />\r\n3.2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Because AntsNest does not permit infringement of intellectual property rights through the AntsNest Services, we will remove all Professionals Content if properly notified that such Site Content or Professionals Content infringes on another&rsquo;s intellectual property rights and at our sole discretion.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n3.3.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;AntsNest does not endorse any Professionals Content or any opinion, recommendation, or advice expressed therein, and we expressly disclaim any and all liability in connection with Professionals Content. You agree that you will not submit Professionals Content that violates the Rules, found or material contrary to applicable local, national, and international laws and regulations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Professionals Content: Ownership &amp; Licenses<br />\r\n4.1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;We do not claim ownership rights over your Professionals Content. However, you grant us the following worldwide, royalty-free and non- exclusive