vices available on or through any such website or resource.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>14.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Children / Minor Policy<br />\r\n14.1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;This website is recommended for use of individuals of age of 18 years or above, but if you are above 13 years of age or older but below 18 years, you may be granted access by providing either of their parents Email IDs and an Email will be sent informing the parent that their ward has registered himself/herself to use the AntsNest Services through this website. Parents of such wards will be liable for damages or losses occurred due to activities or action of their wards and are legally bound by any Acts/ Deeds/ Violations of the AntsNest Terms of Use by their wards. AntsNest shall not be liable for a minor viewing the website without a parent or guardian or misrepresenting their age on the AntsNest Site while registering their account on the AntsNest Platform.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>15.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Indemnity<br />\r\n15.1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;You agree to defend, indemnify and hold AntsNest, our owner, and each of its subsidiaries, affiliates, directors, officers, agents, vendors or other partners, employees and AntsNest moderators harmless from any cla</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n"}

class TermandConditionModel {
  TermandConditionModel({
    String? status,
    String? msg,
    Setting? setting,
  }) {
    _status = status;
    _msg = msg;
    _setting = setting;
  }

  TermandConditionModel.fromJson(dynamic json) {
    _status = json['status'];
    _msg = json['msg'];
    _setting =
        json['setting'] != null ? Setting.fromJson(json['setting']) : null;
  }

  String? _status;
  String? _msg;
  Setting? _setting;

  TermandConditionModel copyWith({
    String? status,
    String? msg,
    Setting? setting,
  }) =>
      TermandConditionModel(
        status: status ?? _status,
        msg: msg ?? _msg,
        setting: setting ?? _setting,
      );

  String? get status => _status;

  String? get msg => _msg;

  Setting? get setting => _setting;

  Map<String, dynamic> toJson() {
    final map = <String, dynamic>{};
    map['status'] = _status;
    map['msg'] = _msg;
    if (_setting != null) {
      map['setting'] = _setting?.toJson();
    }
    return map;
  }
}

